      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ROCK 'N' THE JAM (4) ran over the top from midfield to get the job done with ease by 1.1L over the mile trip. He was the favourite there and now Parnham hops back on board as he steps out to 1800m for the first time today. He's back to his best now and with plenty of upside, he makes plenty of appeal once again. ANTIQUE STAR (5) hasn't been far away her past couple, finishing 1.8L behind ROCK 'N' THE JAM last start. The rise in trip looks right up her alley and she maps to get every chance. Gets a weight swing in her favour and can turn the tables. MISS SKYHIGH (2) comes here on the fresh side today and gets Pike in the saddle replacing the apprentice hoop. She's placed in both attempts over this course and distance and should get every chance for Pike off the inside. Can bounce back in a big way. BAKEEL (1) reunites with his old mate Manoel Nunes as he rises to this trip for the first time. Won't be far away. MADAME MAGIC (3) has claims off a strong effort from the back last start.",
